title: pilgrimage
description:
the unlikely pilgrimage of harold fry by rachel joyce


A shy, housebroken and very ordinary retiree, receives a letter about a long-forgotten friend dying of cancer.

He makes a split-second decision to walk from one end of Britain to the other believing in that doing so, he can save the friend's life . 

He's not physicaly fit, has no hiking gear, no map, no cell phone.

His walk is atonement for making a mess of being a friend, father, and husband.


A life-affirming book with a spot of sentimentality and an awkard ending.
